The defendant Courtney V Robel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Courtney V Robel in court with Attorney Amber K. Rumpf.  Abbey Nickolie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #1.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.   State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Rumpf makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  FINE:  $389.00 & $200 DNA surcharge (to be paid out of cash bail posted ($50.00) and out of cash bail posted on Case #15CM2409 ($50.00) and remainder due at rate of $25.00 per month, commencing 5/2/16, alternate 10 days jail if not paid. 

**Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.**  

**Expunction is conditionally granted after 1 year, upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.**
